parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Front Frame Rail and Control Arms
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the front frame rail and control arms can cause the control arm to break or fall off, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Holes in the front frame rail

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belt retractor can prevent the seat belt from functioning properly, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The rear seat belts do not retract
the rear seat belts do not come out
the rear seat belts are stuck
the rear seat belts do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries. In extreme cases, it can also result in fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire while in motion
flames or smoke emanating from the engine compartment
burning smell or sounds of crackling flames.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to premature wear, damage to other engine components, and potentially catastrophic engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: white smoke or steam emanating from the exhaust
